rst industrial war of the modern era. Illustrated with charts and enriched with source texts, this book documents the extensive changes required of the military to meet this challenge, both in terms of organizational structures and in the methods used to wage war on land, at sea, and in Germany’s colonies.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aWorld War, 1914-1918zGermany. 4aErster Weltkrieg. 4aMilitärgeschichte. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh  aFirst World War.  amilitary history.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA History 2000 - 2014z9783110635836oZDB-23-GHI0 cprintz978348671299540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978348685472540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783486854725423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783486854725/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-GHIc2000d2014